[test planact.it]
# gen258, Italian probe: the SAME derived plan through the Italian trigger
# ("fai un piano per …"). The Italian cues are intent_cue/goal_cue facts; one
# chainer, two languages. Matched on the plainly-normalized raw as well as norm
# because canonicalize_lang rewrites Italian function words.
> fai un piano per portare le catene cue in regime kb-first
< My derived plan for kbfirst migration: 1) locate the OR-chains of calls in the target source (the vocabulary sites); 2) extract the word list each chain encodes; 3) write the words as intent_cue facts in a .p0 file; 4) replace each chain with a kb_cue_match lookup in a patched copy; 5) run the full test suite; the refactor must be behavior-preserving.
> fai un piano per ottenere aiuto esterno
< My derived plan for external help: 1) write what I lack as facts in a needhelp.p0 at the project root; 2) periodically re-read needhelp.p0 to see if someone answered; 3) load the answers as native knowledge and resume the blocked plan.
> esegui il piano kb-first per catene di chiamate a flag in tests/fixtures/orchain/foreign.c
< Executed derived plan for kbfirst migration: 1) orchain_scan found 2 OR-chains of calls to `flag` in tests/fixtures/orchain/foreign.c (5 calls in chains); 2) orchain_vocab extracted 5 cues: alpha, beta, gamma, epsilon, zeta; 3) emit_facts wrote 5 intent_cue facts for 2 chains to tests/fixtures/orchain/foreign.c.cues.p0; 4) patch_chains replaced 2 chains with calls to `lookup` in tests/fixtures/orchain/foreign.c.p0fix and the result still compiles; 5) verify_behavior ran `classify` on 6 probes in both versions; outputs are byte-identical — the patch preserves behavior.
# gen271: the migrated real site, through the Italian trigger — same honest
# "nothing left to migrate" as the English probe, one code path.
> esegui il piano kb-first per catene di chiamate a cue in src/brain/00-lex.c
